Garret Fitzgerald, as Administrator, Appellant, v. Charles Fach, Respondent. Decided January 6, 1890. Appeal from judgment entered upon verdict for plaintiff, and from order denying plaintiff’s motion for a new trial made upon, the minutes. George C. Coffin, for appellant. Thomas F. Grady and Theodore Connolly, for respondent.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., Freedman and Ingraham, JJ.

Per Curiam.

Judgment and order affirmed with costs.
